From: John Jakeman <jdjakem@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 17:42:30 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/5] Disable HVP in loss function and add
 TorchExactGaussianProcess

HVP is temporarily disabled in NegativeLogMarginalLikelihoodLoss due to
suspected bug where trust-constr optimization with HVP sometimes takes
more iterations than without HVP.

New features:
- TorchExactGaussianProcess: GP using autograd for Jacobian computation
- TorchMaternKernel: General Matern kernel supporting arbitrary nu values
- benchmark_hvp.py: Benchmark comparing optimization with/without HVP

Changes:
- Disable HVP in loss._setup_derivative_methods() with TODO to investigate
- Skip HVP-related tests in test_loss_hvp.py and test_loss_dynamic_binding.py
- Add derivative checker tests for TorchExactGaussianProcess
