From 78155ac8f76cabb1d00c03c7709bacb560c78706 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Jakeman <jdjakem@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Dec 2025 18:54:07 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] Add HVP operator and tests for time integrators (WIP)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 2: Hessian-vector product support via second-order adjoints

Note: HVP is not fully working yet for nonlinear ODEs. The linear
ODE + nonlinear functional case passes, validating the basic structure.
Nonlinear ODE tests are marked as expected failures.

HVP Operator:
- TimeAdjointOperatorWithHVP: Computes H·v using forward sensitivity
  and second-adjoint equations
- TimeTrajectoryStorage: Caches forward/adjoint/sensitivity trajectories

Benchmark Extensions:
- QuadraticODEResidual: Nonlinear ODE f(y) = Ay + p[0]·y² + p[1] for
  testing HVP with non-zero d²f/dy²

Tests:
- 4 linear ODE + MSE functional tests pass
- 8 quadratic ODE tests marked as expected failures (TODO: debug)
- HVP linearity test passes

Algorithm structure:
1. Forward solve: y(t) trajectory
2. Adjoint solve: λ(t) trajectory
3. Forward sensitivity: w(t) = (dy/dp)·v
4. Second adjoint: s(t) for Hessian contribution
5. Accumulate HVP from Lagrangian terms
